BP Plc (BP/)  had a  power outage  at its
Texas City, Texas, oil refinery late yesterday, according to the
local police department.  The outage occurred about 11 p.m. local time, according to
a statement by the police. A shelter-in-place order advising
residents to stay indoors and turn off air conditioners has been
issued, according to the statement.  The 475,000 barrel-a-day plant was the site of a 2005
explosion that killed 15 workers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Schmollinger in  Singapore  at 
